Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a novel algorithm that combines Support Vector Machine and Evolutionary Optimization to solve Dynamic Multi-Objective Optimization Problems. This falls under the scope of Neural and Evolutionary Computing.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses Support Vector Machine as a key component of the proposed algorithm. SVM is a popular machine learning technique, and the paper discusses its use in detail. Hence, this paper can be categorized under Machine Learning.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an AI-based algorithm that can solve Dynamic Multi-Objective Optimization Problems. This falls under the scope of Artificial Intelligence.
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes an algorithm that uses a combination of SVM and Evolutionary Optimization to solve Dynamic Multi-Objective Optimization Problems. This falls under the scope of Data Structures and Algorithms.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an algorithm that can be used to solve Dynamic Multi-Objective Optimization Problems, which is a problem that arises in many control systems. Hence, this paper can be categorized under Systems and Control.
